item.description:
Grunt is a JavaScript/Node.js based task runner in some ways very similar to Makefile and Apache Ant. It requires Node.js beforehand, just like Ant needs a Java Runtime. After installing Node.js, Grunt command line can be installed as following.
npm install -g grunt-cli  Grunt tasks are defined in a configuration Gruntfile.js (JavaScript) or Gruntfile.coffee (CoffeeScript).
// Grunt's wrapper function module.exports = function(grunt) { // let's grunt in here };  Grunt plugins and tasks grunt.
